Very Poor Customer Service and a Filthy Environment!!!!! See pictures for detail. I have been going to Lesaac for more than four years. The waitresses don't even greet you when you arrive. They give you the menu, take your order, and disappear right after that. Another waitress brings the food after several minutes, and no one will check on you the whole time you're in there. Even to pay a bill, you have to get up and ask for it. Another big reason I'm writing this review is that the last time I was dining in, there were flies all over the food. We couldn't even eat our meal probably and didn't finish it. The waiters noticed this and asked if the food wasn't right. I mentioned to her that there were flies all over the food, and we couldn't eat it. She looked at me and walked off without saying anything and brought the bills like I said something offensive or insulted her. By far, this is the craziest customer service I ever encountered in my life. I don't think I would ever go back again.  Owner/Management: Please train and manage your employees properly. Even fast food restaurants provide some level of customer service!

There are dozens of other Ethiopian restaurants within walking distance from here - any of which would easily be a better experience for you. Food? Overpriced and not nearly as appetizing as the price would suggest. Ordered a ~$10 plate with water and, really, I could've done better heading over to the Chik-Fil-A or Nandos a few blocks over. I didn't order any special drink and just asked for water. They gave me tap water. Tap water. Any other place would have given purified water. Lesaac's? Tap. That experience was punctuated when it finally came to pay for the "food" they served. I gave them a $10 and waited for my change. I waited for a couple minutes after paying, saying nothing since I assumed they could handle at least that. Eventually, one of the women asked me to leave.  Yeah, in short, you can do better than this place. Silver Spring is a large city with many other small restaurants more deserving of your money than this place.
